Package uk.ac.rdg.resc.edal.feature

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DiscreteFeature<P,DO>
    A Feature whose domain consists of a finite number of domain objects, each of which is associated with a single measurement value from each Feature member.
    Feature<P>
    Superclass for all Feature types.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractDiscreteFeature<P,DO>
    A partial implementation of a Feature containing common functionality
    GridFeature
    An implementation of a Feature whose domain is a GridDomain
    MapFeature
    An implementation of a Feature whose domain is a DiscreteHorizontalDomain.
    PointCollectionFeature
    A feature consisting of measurements at a series of HorizontalPositions fixed vertically and temporally (i.e.
    PointFeature
    A measurement at a single 4D point
    PointSeriesFeature
    A measurement of a time series at a point
    ProfileFeature
    A measurement of a vertical profile at a point
    TrajectoryFeature
    A Feature representing values over a 1-dimensional domain of time-ordered points, where each point has a distinct value in 4-dimensional space
